    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-01-25T10:24:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-01-25T10:24:00-05:00" n="751"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d751">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/6222: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gade</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-01-25T17:00:00+01:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 25, 1920—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>77. I am credibly informed that British Government has notified Esthonian
                    Government of its satisfaction at conclusion of armistice with Bolsheviks. This
                    being known to Latvian Government will greatly influence its present
                    negotiations in Moscow. French here indignant.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gade</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
